Performance Impact:
-------------------

Expected CI Runtime:
- Unit tests: ~5-10 min per module (5 modules = 25-50 min parallel)
- Integration tests: ~2-5 min
- Performance tests: ~22 min (full load profile)
- Security tests: ~3-5 min
- E2E tests: ~10-15 min
- Total (all parallel): ~25-30 min

Resource Requirements:
- GitHub Actions runners: 5 concurrent (unit test matrix)
- PostgreSQL service: 1 per unit test job
- k6 load generator: 200 concurrent VUs peak
- Playwright browser: 1 per E2E test

Cost Optimization:
- Path-filtered triggers (only run when needed)
- Parallel matrix execution (unit tests)
- Shared browser fixtures (E2E)
- Cached dependencies (pip, playwright)
- Continue-on-error for non-blocking checks

Quality Gates:
--------------

Enforced:
✅ Unit test coverage ≥ 70%
✅ Performance P95 < 2000ms
✅ Error rate < 1%
✅ No HIGH severity security issues
✅ Successful E2E test execution

Optional (warnings):
⚠️  Medium severity security issues (reported but don't fail)
⚠️  Integration tests (if secrets not configured)
⚠️  Performance tests (if base URL not accessible)

Risk Assessment:
----------------

Low Risk:
- Well-established tools (pytest, playwright, k6, bandit)
- Comprehensive error handling in workflows
- Continue-on-error for optional checks
- Clear documentation and examples

Medium Risk:
- Claude API dependency (requires valid API key)
- External service integration tests (n8n, Plane, Supabase)
- Performance test load (requires production-like environment)

Mitigation:
- API key validation before execution
- Graceful handling of missing secrets
- Performance tests optional (manual trigger)
- Clear error messages for troubleshooting

